A Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) delegate, Mr Tanko Rossi Sabo, has shared all the money he made from the recent presidential primary of the party with his community in Sanga LGA of Kaduna state. According to a former Special Assistant Media to late Governor Yakubu Yakowa, Reuben Buhari, Sabo spent N7million alone on the less privileged in his community.   Southeast: Pupils, candidate defying sit-at-home to attend…     Why we’re hosting tourism conference, by Buhari     How govt can make tech education attractive, by FCET Provost   “He bought jerseys, paid school fees and hospital fees. He distributed the rest to other support groups. “Whatever is the argument on whether he was right in collecting the money or not, my consolation is that hundreds of the less privileged in his community are smiling today. For that, I say well done Tanko,” Buhari said. Sabo was one of Kaduna delegates at the National Convention of the Peoples Democratic Party ( PDP) where former Vice President Atiku Abubakar emerged as presidential candidate of the opposition party.